Command                                       Meaning

git --version                                 Show installed git version
git config --global user.name 'name'          Configure username
git config --global user.email 'email'        Configure email
git config user.name                          Show configured username
git config user.email                         Show configured email

git clone 'github repo link'                  Clones repo to current directory
cd 'directory'                                Go to 'directory'
cd ..                                         Leave one directory
dir                                           Show all directories
cd                                            Show content of directory
mkdir 'directory'                             Create directory
rmdir 'directory'                             Remove directory
touch 'file.type'                             Create new file
rm 'file.type'                                Remove file
git init                                      Create repo

git branch                                    Show current branch
git branch -r                                 Show all branches
git branch -vv                                Show tracking branches
git checkout 'branch'                         Go to 'branch'
git status                                    Check which files are changed
git add 'file'                                Add 'file' to staging area
git add .                                     Add all files to staging area
git commit -m "commit message"                Commit change with message
git push                                      Push change
git push -u origin 'branch'                   Set upstream branch
